NPCName "Lacey"
Location "Top floor, Club Seven Deadly"
Description "Lacey’s role in the game is to make Club Seven Deadly feel more impactful. She was/is the madame of the club’s brothel, although, before the war, she still entertained some of Seven Deadly’s most prestigious clients personally. See expanded Circle Junction design document for details."
Unknown_Desc "a ghoulified woman in fine clothes."
Known_Desc "Lacey, the pre-war madame of Club Seven Deadly's brothel."
Detailed_Desc "She seems alert but occupied by her thoughts."

/* Float message nodes */

Floatnode "Lacey_float01"
notes "Lacey's default floats."
{
"Any day now... the big payday.",
"Willow would've liked this setup.",
"They think they’re untouchable. Not for long.",
"The signal’s still broadcasting. Good.",
"Damn rich boys. Always dirty under the polish.",
"Vault-Tec’s sins, neatly packaged. Just waiting.",
"My girls deserved better. They still do.",
"Who says a madame can't be a queen?",
"Bastards always slip up. Always.",
"The fat cats fall, and I rise. Soon enough."
}
Floatnode "Lacey_float02"
notes "Lacey's combat floats."
{
"Should’ve stayed outta my house, sugar.",
"This ain’t my first fight, sweetheart.",
"I’ve buried better than you.",
"Get out, or get dead!",
"You want my secrets? Pay in blood!",
"Another dead fool in my club."
}

